<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="337" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="337">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="337">
The separation of this species from other species is explained in the key. In the genitalia, the dense bush of long spines at the posterior end of vesica is characteristic, and the genital characters readily separate it from the externally similar but smaller 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. joannisi" pageId="0" pageNumber="337" rank="species" species="joannisi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="337">P. joannisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see the key for further details.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
